\n<Marion>I've reached the maximum level up possible with the Grow
Cores!
\n<Marion>For now, this is as strong as Eury can get.

\n<Eury>...When you put it that way, it feels kind of sad to hit a
limit.

\n<Marion>Well, you haven't been a modified girl for that long, so
it's to be expected.

\n<Eury>By the way, do you think I have a chance of beating Makina-
senpai with my current combat abilities?

\n<Marion>Well, if Makina was completely standing still, maybe you
could win?
\n<Marion>You've got potential, so keep at it.
All Grow Cores have been used.

Your level has returned to 1, and the Grow Cores for the
reduced levels will be extracted. Will you perform
maintenance?

\n<Marion>Voila, maintenance complete. I've extracted all the cores
we've used so far.

\n<Marion>In your current state, you're just a Level 1 weakling, so be
careful not to go monster hunting like this.
\n<Marion>...Why do you ask about that name?
\n<Marion>That's absurd. Ruin was creating something called Manoloids?

\n<Marion>To begin with, that guy completely cut off all contact with
me after I completed the modified girl.
\n<Marion>So, I had assumed he died from the monster damage...
\n<Marion>...Well, at least I thought we were.
\n<Marion>Now, let me read that letter of yours.
You and I were good friends, both aspiring to be engineers.

But the one whose achievements were always recognized was
only you.

All of my discoveries at the time were condemned as
dangerous and discarded.

While I couldn't succeed in anything, you somehow completed
the modified girl who would save the world.
I still remember that moment even now.

Crushed by a sense of inferiority, I thought I never wanted
to see you again.

Even after the modified girl was defeated once and the world
was dominated by monsters, I continued to live in hiding.
...A few months after the original monster was defeated,

I met someone for the first time who acknowledged my
technology.
I followed that person and continued to create Manoloids.

My Manoloids will one day defeat the modified girl you
created.

With that single-minded purpose, I became an ally of the
monsters.
Seeing me as I am now, what do you think?
\n<Marion>Wasn't that enough to not turn to monsters?
\n<Eury>...He said he was in Tenge Street.
\n<Marion>Sorry, but I can't go there. Find him and bring him here!

\n<Marion>Creating monsters is a serious crime, not just terrorism. He
needs to wake up soon...!

\n<Makina>By the way, there's a forest near Tengatsu City. It seems
there was a \C[24]large monster reaction\C[0] there.

\n<Makina>Can you \C[24]patrol\C[0] during the daytime? If there are
any suspicious traces, we'll need to go defeat it at night.

\n<Makina>Take this with you, you can't fight if you run out of
bullets.

parameters.name: 【会話08_03】ありがとうございます。

parameters:
\n<Makina>I have my own mission. I'm operating from a different city,
but the situation is urgent.

\n<Makina>Sorry, but I must go now. Eury, be very careful and tackle
your mission without letting your guard down.

\n<Makina>...If you lose to the monster, who knows what will happen.
Eury, really, don't push yourself too hard.

\n<Makina>Eury, I have a message. There's a possibility that monsters
have taken up residence in an abandoned school near Tengatsu
Street.
\n<Makina>I'm asking for a patrol during the daytime.

\n<Makina>Also, let me teach you a method to efficiently explore large
dungeons.
LL_InfoPopupWIndowMV showWindow 解放：\i[82]\C[14]ダッシュモード\C[0] 120 auto auto 0

\n<Makina>It's a method where you use smoke bombs to escape from
monsters and aim for the deeper areas. You might not be able
to defeat many monsters, but it's efficient for taking down
bosses.

parameters.name: 【会話09_05】ありがとうございますっ♪

parameters: \n<Eury>Yes, it's going fairly well! How about you, Makina-senpai?
\n<Makina>...I'm having a bit of a tough time.

\n<Makina>That's not it. I can't find a way to help people who have
been poisoned by the monsters.

\n<Makina>We're gathering data on the monsters, and Marion is rushing
to develop an antidote, but...

\n<Makina>There are already many people who have become victims and
are currently suffering.

\n<Makina>We must do something about the monster's poison as soon as
possible. I'm sorry, but I must go now.
\n<Eury>...Yes! I will also do my best with what I need to do!

\n<Makina>Eury, another directive. There's a den of monsters near
Tengeki Street.

\n<Makina>As soon as you find it, infiltrate immediately and defeat
the monster leader.

\n<Makina>Also, I found some Glow Cores, so I'll hand them over. Use
them to strengthen yourself.
LL_InfoPopupWIndowMV showWindow 入手：\i[307]\C[14]グロウコア\C[0] 120 auto auto 0
\n<Eury>Three of them!? Thank you so much!

\n<Makina>...About my mission, the antidote seems to be nearing
completion soon.

\n<Makina>Once its safety is confirmed, it should be able to save
those suffering from poison.

\n<Makina>Eury. Are there any people suffering from poison in Tengeki
Street?

\n<Makina>Understood. There's a surplus, so if needed, you can get it
from Marion.
\n<Makina>Then, I'll be on my way soon.

\n<Makina>Eury, it's an emergency. \C[2]A suspicious base has been
spotted in the vicinity of Tengeki Street.

\n<Makina>It's possible that it's related to the mechanical-like
monster executives you've been fighting up until now.
\n<Makina>Eury... you've really done well to get this far.

\n<Makina>At first, I was nothing but anxious... but the number of
monsters has definitely decreased, and you've defeated
strong enemies.

\n<Makina>As for that base... we have absolutely no idea what might be
lurking inside.
\n<Makina>Approach with caution, and make sure you come back alive.
\n<Makina>The mission in Tengatsu Street seems to have ended safely.
\n<Eury>Yes! It's all thanks to you, Makina-senpai!
\n<Eury>I'll continue to do my best as a modified girl!
\n<Ruin>Well, I owe Eury a lot... for various things.
\n<Ruin>So, I'll help out with what I can.

\n<Ruin>But for some reason, \C[2]Marion\C[0] absolutely tells me
